   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-accepting-a" image="QW_PrairieTown.dds" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-accepting-b" mid="8"><![CDATA[<html>That not exactly I was saying...</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="7"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>Ahhh... You're that young adventurer from Prairie You've made quite a name for yourself already, hmm?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-accepting-b" image="QN_BlackSmith_dorin.dds" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-accepting-e" mid="13"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="9"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>Oh ho, and modest, too! Well, my brother Blacksmith Dorin told me good things about you. I was hoping you would drop by. I wanted to see for myself the kind of person my grouch of a brother would speak so warmly of!</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-accepting-c" image="QW_ManaRidge.dds" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-accepting-d" mid="15"><![CDATA[<html>That not exactly I was saying...</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="14"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>Ahhh... You're that young adventurer from Mana Ridge. You've made quite a name for yourself already, hmm?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-accepting-d" image="QN_BlackSmith_dorin.dds" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-accepting-e" mid="17"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="16"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>Oh ho, and modest, too! I must admit, I wasn't really sure what to expect. My brother Blacksmith Borin spoke quite highly of you but, well, he's not quite right in the head. I'm sure you noticed, yes? I was hoping you'd stop by...frankly, I couldn't imagine who could stand to help Borin out as you did!</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-accepting-e" image="QW_CataractGateway.dds" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-accepting-f" mid="20"><![CDATA[<html>(………)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="18"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>Indeed, indeed. Well, I suppose I ought help you, since you were so kind to my brother.<BR>Let's see... The thing is, Calderock Village is a place for tough, experienced adventurers. I'm not sure we have any newbie gear for someone like yourself...</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-accepting-f" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-accepting-g" mid="23"><![CDATA[<html>Wow...ah, no, I guess not.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="21"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>(Corin study you closely.)<BR>Don't worry too much. I have some odds and ends around that I'd be happy to give you. I hope you're not too attached to that garbage you're wearing now, though. You aren't, are you?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-accepting-g" image="QS_Default.dds" itemindex="336732192">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-accepting-h" mid="26"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="24"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>Right! Let's see what we have for you...<BR>Here, these are Common Starlight Fragments. I've got some left over from crafting some simple rings. These should be good for crafting a new ring for you. Sound good?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-accepting-h" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-accepting-acceptted" mid="28"><![CDATA[<html><FONT color=#086171>Accept quest.</FONT></html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="27"><![CDATA[<html>$Ring Production I$</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-1" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-1-a" mid="30"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="29"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>Alright. There are two materials needed for crafting a basic ring.<BR>Onyx Fragments are one, and these Common Starlight Fragments are the other.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-1-a" image="QS_Default.dds" itemindex="336617472">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-1-b" mid="32"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="31"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>I assume you have plenty of Onyx Fragments. They're quite common...you can find them almost everywhere. The Starlight Fragments are the rare ones...you're lucky I still have a few leftovers. Heehee...</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-1-b" image="QS_Default.dds" itemindex="336732192">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-1-c" mid="37"><![CDATA[<html> Yes, sir. </html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="33"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>I tell you what. I hate giving things away for nothing, even if you did help my brothers, so let me give you a little quiz on crafting before I give you these Starlight Fragments. I also hate giving things away if I think they're going to be wasted, so this kills two birds with one stone. Sound okay to you?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-1-c" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-1-d" mid="50"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="38"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>Great. Okay, so items can be crafted at any town's blacksmith. Items are mainly divided into <FONT color=#a82424>Weapons</FONT>, <FONT color=#a82424>Armor</FONT>, and <FONT color=#a82424>Accessories</FONT>. Each town has different items that can be crafted, as well.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-1-d" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-1-e" mid="51"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="40"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>My brothers and I are all at different skill levels. We can only craft items up to a certain level, so be sure you talk to the right blacksmith.<BR>(Prairie Town, Mana Ridge - up to Lv. 10)<BR>(Calderock - up to Lv. 24)<BR>(Saint Haven - above Lv. 24.)</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-1-e" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-1-f" mid="44"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="42"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>There are two ways to craft items.<BR>(These are shown on the left and right sides of the Craft Item List.)</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-1-f" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-1-g" mid="48"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="45"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>The difference is how many materials you want to use. The more materials you use, the higher your chances of successfully crafting your item are.<BR>Using less materials is risky, but if you're lucky, you'll have more materials leftover.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-1-g" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-1-h" mid="53"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="49"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>Now, here's the most important thing! Crafted items have special bonuses that can be selected, depending on the item. When you make a new item, you can see which bonuses you can choose from.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-1-h" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-2" mid="55"><![CDATA[<html>Sound risky..</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="54"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>So, you can make items with the exact features you want...if you're lucky. If you're not, you may end up with unwanted features, or your crafting may fail entirely! Heehee!</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-2" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-2-a" mid="57"><![CDATA[<html> Yes, sir. </html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="56"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>Hey, no risk, no gain! Okay, enough lecturing.<BR>Time for your quiz. Listen carefully, and you should do fine.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-2-a" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-2-b" mid="60"><![CDATA[<html>Weapons</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-2-b" mid="61"><![CDATA[<html>Armor</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-2-b" mid="62"><![CDATA[<html>Accessories</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-2-c" mid="63"><![CDATA[<html>Hound</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="58"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>Which of the following cannot be crafted?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-2-b" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-2-a" mid="65"><![CDATA[<html>Maybe I should take this a little more seriously...</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="64"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>You're...you're joking, right? That wasn't even a serious question! One of those things is a LIVING BEING!! How in the world are you going to craft an animal?!<BR>( Corin takes a deep breath.)<BR>I'm just going to forget you said anything. Let me ask you again.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-2-c" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-2-d" mid="68"><![CDATA[<html>True!</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-2-e" mid="69"><![CDATA[<html>False!</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="66"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>Good. That was just to make sure you're awake. Heehee!<BR>Next question! True or false: There are a total of three ways to craft an item. You can use more materials for better odds, less materials for lower odds, or no materials and use money instead.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-2-d" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-2-a" mid="71"><![CDATA[<html>That was quite a silly mistake to make...</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="70"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>Wrong! How are you going to craft items with just money? How do you think I make all these amazing pieces of equipment, chanting magic spells?! Wake up and try it again!</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-2-e" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-2-f" mid="73"><![CDATA[<html>Items can be crafted only through the blacksmiths in each town.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-2-f" mid="77"><![CDATA[<html>Crafted items have a number of options that can be randomly applied.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-2-g" mid="78"><![CDATA[<html>Crafting materials can be bought from blacksmiths and general stores.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="72"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>Good! I see now that you are using your common sense. Last question! Which of the following is not true?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-2-f" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-2-a" mid="80"><![CDATA[<html>Ooh, that was tricky...!</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="79"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>Unfortunately, you are wrong. When was the last time you saw raw crafting materials for sale, hmm? Once more!</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n025_trader_corin-2-g" image="QS_Default.dds" itemindex="336732192">
      <talk_answer link_index="n025_trader_corin-2-h" mid="82"><![CDATA[<html>Thank you!</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="81"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Corin$<BR>Excellent! Thank you for taking the time to listen. As promised, here's your Common Starlight Fragment.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
